caption: SO. GOOD.
The wait staff was friendly. The shrimp and grits and shrimp omelet were  amazing.
Food was great and waitstaff made sure we had room for the baby stroller

We arrived home yesterday from our 6 day stay which was Wonderful!  Monday after we woke up I added our names to The Ruby Slipper online wait-list. We walked up to check in and were seated immediately. I enjoyed their french toast bites and my wife had one of their breakfast sandwiches. Service was wonderful. Ruby slipper ⭐⭐⭐⭐
Nolan was the best! We love you Nolan! Good was good vibe was great and so happy we ate here.  We were very hung over and Nolan and the other staff treated us very well!
Love the food! Wait times were long, but it was worth the wait 😊
Best breakfast I have had in a long time...the peach belini was awesome.  Great service!
my favorite place to eat here you won't regret it try the bloody Mary!
Loved the bene

Such a great breakfast spot with good food, excellent service, tasty drinks and nice atmosphere. The staff was kind and took the time to offer recommendations about other things to do around town. Our server was awesome. Highly recommend!
Amazing food and exceptional customer service. We had to go back a second time it was sooooo good.

I know where my first stop for breakfast will be the next time I’m in town! My family visited this location a few days ago for breakfast. The menu here has something for everyone. Each dish was flavorful and presented very nicely. Our server was also friendly and attentive throughout our entire meal. Yes, you may wait a long time (get on the waitlist) but it’s worth it!
This place was amazing. The wait was short for a NOLA brunch and the staff was amazing. The food was delicious and I ordered what my waitress suggested. Will definitely be recommending and returning.
French toast bites are delicious!
The peacemaker with my choice of the hot smoke salmon & bayou shrimp Benedicts !!! So yummy ! Also had the seasonal beignets and they were so delicious!

I am very disappointed in the service. There was a party of one inside waiting before me in line. This person directly in front of me was offered a table inside or outside. He chose to sit outside. When I requested the inside seat that was just offered and declined by the previous party, I was told that the only option of seating was outside. This would have been fine if the person in front of me was not given another seating option and did not have allergies that are triggered by humidity. I would rather spend my money elsewhere, and I would recommend that you do the same.
Food was excellent! Norman was amazing!
The Eggs Benedict Though!!!!!!!
Great breakfast in New Orleans. Make sure to try the French toast bits. So yummy.
The best omelet you ever ate period .yes
The service was great! The food was delicious!! They had this new dish, crawfish Benedict 😋, that tasted absolutely delicious!!! We loved it so much!!! @chica_foodie for more pics.

Cheap, delicious food. Loved the option to scan not only the menu but also the method of payment. Making everything so easy and safe. Tables were wiped down between guest which I observed. Was seated fast. No complaints . Ordered the French toast bites and hit chicken. Delicious. Recommend
Best food and service. Brought my daughter for great fried green tomatoes and  beignets with coffee.  Awesome service.
Food was okay but pretty standard nothing jumped out at me
The staff was very friendly.  We got drinks to go and they were good.
Love the breakfast here
The food was absolutely delicious! The down side was waiting almost an hour to be seated; after their online waiting list said 30 minutes.  Still well worth the wait.
Awesome food and very friendly staff. Definitely recommend checking this place out for breakfast. I got the King Cake French toast and my husband got the Peacemaker Benedict.
All the Eggs Benedict are amazing. My personal favorites Cochon and St. Charles with hot sauce.

The food here is amazing. The vibe is very relaxed and the service is on point. Our food came out fast each time, at least within 20 minutes after ordering. We will definitely be returning when we visit again.
Food good 👍they really nice love this place would go here again.
Food was awesome and very worth the experience. Service was slow but that is par for the course in the french quarter.
Cute place. Great food.

We had a terrific breakfast here on our last morning in New Orleans. Service was attentive and friendly.  My vanilla latte was super hot and delicious! I got the Southern Breakfast and my friend got the 3 little pigs omelette.  Everything was great and the  food was hot. This is a great breakfast spot and there are several locations nearby.
Great food
Amazing food!
Great food and great people
Great biscuits and gray.  Friendly staff

First time visiting NOLA and we were lyfor a breakfast place. Well we weren't wrong to try Ruby Slipper Cafe. The food is delicious and the atmosphere is great. The servers are nice and very attentive. Panackes are a must. The eggs Benedict are delicious and gray coffee as well.
Great service and great food. It's a good environment and the place lives up to it's reputation. It's definitely worth going at least once to enjoy the meals here.

Heard alot about this place so couldn't wait to go. It did not disappoint! Had the Eggs Cochon and Eggs Blackstone. Best Benedicts we've ever had. The biscuit just dissappears under all that goodness and the hollandaise sauce is amazing. That's usually my least favorite part and here, it's won me over.

Did a walk in and got checked in, estimate was an hour. Was told that when your close to next the company would text you. Received the informative your in line text.  Waited an hour. Went back for another estimate, another hour. Still 17th in line. The store closed a few hours later and I still havent got the text my table is ready.
Excellent food, great staff
Great food and drinks

Norman was our waiter and he was one of the best we have had on our trip. The food was great but he made it better. This place is awesome and the food tasted like homemade love. We Love it and we will return when we come back.
This place makes the most amazing eggs Benedict I’ve ever had in my life! Our waitress Patty was friendly and gave us some nice travel ideas. Definitely a great place for breakfast!

This was an amazing place! The food is unique and all very delicious. We received a welcome and service with a smile. Try the Trifecta--which is a trio of different types of Eggs Benedict. I highly recommend this when visiting New Orleans.
Sweet Heat Chicken and French Toast bites. OMG
The food was great! Very fresh and good portions. The Bloody Mary’s were just okay. Weak and $12 even though the menu said $10.
The French toast with the praline butterscotch sauce just melts in your mouth.  Took a order back to the room and same great taste
Loved the story of how this place started. Great food and service.
Coffee was good. The kitchen left off my friend green tomato from my southern breakfast order which is why they got 4 stars instead of 5
Absolutely marvelous!
This place is a truly 5 star experience! Atmosphere was great and the food was amazing!!
Delicious.

BBQ shrimp and grits were AWSOME. Fried green tomatoes were on point as well. Chicken and French toast bites really good too!  Highly recommend. Went around 9am on a Sunday and was able to get sat at a table right away.

Check in through Yelp!! We waited a couple minutes but it was ok. I had the breakfast sandwich and my husband has the biscuits and gravy with the chicken. It was all so much food!! But soo good.  I was disappointed that I had seen some items on the menu but they were based on locations and the one we ate at didn’t have those items. Thankfully the breakfast sandwich was still delicious.  Totally worth the wait and the hype
The most incredible food and service.

Poor management. My party of two checked in at 11 on Saturday was told it would be a 30 minute wait,no problem. After waiting a hour and a half and watching large parties being seated we left. I understand more people equals more money but this should not be excepted. We left and went to another restaurant.

The Ruby Slipper Cafe is a local and tourist favorite. They will always be busy and for good reason. Make sure to reserve online so you can get in the que. Don't be alarmed if you are number 21, breakfast goes by quickly and they can serve and flip tables fast. What I love to do is get a drink while we are waiting to enjoy. We got the Irish coffee which tasted amazing. I've also had their bloody mary and mimosa before. Once seated we had already checked out the menu and knew what to order. We had a crab omelet and the French toast banana foster. Both were amazing and very filling. The service was good but nothing to talk about. But the food and drinks make it worth it. We love all the different locations around the city. It makes it easy to dine there no matter where you are at.
Drink was a little to strong for 9:30 a.m. lol
Ate a specialty for the city. Something I wouldn't prepare at home. It's nice being a tourist in my own town.

Great wait staff and unique menu but there is always a wait to be seated. They need someone other than the host/hostess and waitstaff to clear and reset tables. This would reduce wait time by half and increase their sales, when they can turn their tables faster. As a retired waitress I can see where they can improve. Food is great and they take menu changes without messing up your order, that can be challenging for kitchen staff. I will be back!

Amazing eggs Benedict and breakfast tacos. Came back for a second morning of takeout because it was so good-they forgot the hollandaise sauce. They comped that part of the meal and gave us some candied bacon to make up for it as well. A+
Outstanding food and service. Highly recommend! We went for breakfast and it was, in a word, wonderful. I don't want to spoil it...but here'a a hint: French toast...
Really great spot for Breakfast
A hidden jewel off the beaten path. Highly recommended!
Bbq Shrimp and grits was really great
Best breakfast I've ever had!
I loved their corned beef egg Benedict sandwich! Loved the coffee and the mug that I had to take home a mug for myself :) Great service as well. I’d def come back when I visit New Orleans again!
Everything was absolutely delicious. The service was great as well. The French toast bites are my favorite, the praline sauce was the perfect touch!
The staff is very attentive. The shrimp & grits was delicious! Too much food for 1 sitting but who am I to complain? Pricing is very fair. Looking forward to my next visit.
Loved my huge cappuccino and perfectly creamy cheese grits! Our waiter, Norman was very welcoming.
Food was delicious and the service was great! We sat outside and had two of their unique benedicts. Perfect brunch spot for good food and great cocktails!
Just delicious! Service was amazing. Drinks were well made and strong!

If you don’t eat here you are seriously missing out!  Pancakes are dinner plate size and you get 2. I ordered the Eggs Cochon. Lightly seasoned shredded pork on a biscuit with perfectly poached eggs and hollandaise. Add a peach Bellini. Esta was our server. Very good server. Took good care of us, and my Bellini. Very clean. Staff was keeping up with cleaning the entire time we were there. Highly recommend. We will be back before we leave the area.
Had to upload a qr code reader on my phone to see a menu but other than that, very good service and food.
One of the best breakfast restaurants I have ever been to. We are planning on going back tomorrow before we leave town so we can try something else.
We loved it so much we will definitely be back..
Quick lunch after a morning at the Aquarium of the America's. It was fast, easy and very good.
Excellent service.  Breakfast was unique, very flavorful and very generous portions.  We will return.
A wonderful brunch spot with great bloody mary's
Excellent breakfast.  Great food and service.

Similar to a place in KY/Cincy called 'First Watch', this place offers everyday breakfast but a level up. Whether you're in the mood for irish coffee, a funky eggs benedict, pancakes/french toast, or pastry, this place is prepped. I would recommend breakfast here to anyone.  The texmex breakfast is really good.
Giant cup of spicy vanilla latte and breakfast of eggs, bacon, grits and biscuit for breakfast. Yum.

Their hollandaise sauces were amazing and the Irish coffee very boozy! Only 2 negatives I can say is some of the biscuits were a bit hard and chewy and the shrimp on mine was a bit undercooked. Everyone in the staff was delightful!

If decisions aren't your thing, the Ruby Slipper let's your choose The Peacemaker, which is a choice of two of their original and suspiciously delicious benedicts. Pair that with a freshly made cappuccino and cinnamon-crusted French Toast bites and become the envy of all your out-of-town friends.
OMG! Visiting New Orleans for the 1st time on my birthday.. This place right here was amazing!! When ever I visit again,this is one stop I'm definitely making👍👍

The Ruby Slipper was recommended for breakfast by a local tour guide while we were shopping and it was one of the highlights of my trip to New Orleans.  The staff was very engaging, friendly and talkative!! They helped my fiance with his hangover and the food was awesome!!! Definitely will go back!!!
Food was a little cold and the portion of the Costa Rican breakfast on the chorizo was not enough.
Very good breakfast & coffee.
Great French toast bites
The food was delicious.  The waitress was amazing
The line is worth the wait. Delcious food a tad pricey. $10.00 for a glass of mimosa.
Service was great. Food was good but the grits need more flavor.

Had breakfast here with my daughter during a trip to NOLA. The breakfast sandwich and her shrimp and grits were amazing. The Big Easy was big and went down easy! Yum! Our waitress was so sweet and made sure we were well taken care of during our breakfast!
Amazing food and service. Mimosas are delicious and our food was killer. The cheese grit cake under my fish was so good. Really loved the atmosphere and kind and quick service!

Plenty of flavor to the coffee, not too strong. Had the migas. Didn't look too appealing at first but after adding the sauce and pico de gallo it was amazing. Probably best if you like sour cream though like I do. Polite and sociable staff, a nice change from home. I enjoyed it a lot as a tourist.
Best breakfast i have ever had!!

We stopped by on our way out of New Orleans and we were welcomed by great attitude ( and probably a big smile under their masks). The food was delicious 😋! And a great price for the area!! Definitely one of our favorite stops for next time we visit!
Relaxed staff, good food but portions are rather small for the price.
Delicious food! Candy bacon is essentially heaven!
AEESOME!
We had a lovely time! Delicious Benedicts and lived their vanilla iced coffee!
Absolutely loved the breakfast you will not be disappointed
Great Service! Try the Bacon / Pecan Pancake!!
Food was soo good. Big Easy Mimosa was tasty, good amount of champagne! Customer service was excellent. Highly recommend
This place has never disappoint me. Their food is phenomenal! I absolutely love Norman!!!
Best friend green tomatoes I've ever had!! One of the tastiest breakfast restaurants we experienced on our NOLA visit.
My favorite.
Food was delicious
Very great meal and best wait staff!!!

Excellent....  I ordered the Corned Beef & Hash Lord .....it was tender, the potatoes added in with shredded cheddar.. Hold the sauce & horseradish. The fresh spanich as a garnish added a crispy freshness.. mm mmmm
Very expensive for basic brunch. Wasn't that impressed with the meal. The best thing going was the mimosas.
Absolutely delicious and the staff was fun and friends.
Service was excellent food was excellent. They are friendly and food comes out fast no long wait at all.
NICE PPL, LOVED THE FRENCH TOAST BITES!! COMING FROM NY :)
Love it!!! Blessed the hands of the food was the only thing I had to say about the place!! Excellent eating!! The st. Charles dish is everything!
You really must try this place, there isn't a disappointing thing on the menu. Check in with Yelp to get in line before you arrive!
Great
Best Eggs Benedict I have ever had. Literal tears of joy.
Good service and food
Omelet was great
Great food! Definitely worth the trip
Shrimp and grits were good, but 1 shrimp in each dish weren't clean. Had to clean them myself! Biscuit wasn't soft and hot either. Great service, I'll go back!
Great food and service. Will be back.

There are not enough words to describe the greatness of this restaurant. Their message for the business pictured below was heartwarming. The staff were gracious and welcoming. Paul,  our waiter,  asked our names and made us so comfortable we came back our third day. And then the food and drinks were simply perfect. We will be back every time we make it to New Orleans. This is a not to miss brunch restaurant and worth a wait for a seat.

Food was very salty and only one person ate their food because it was something basic. The burger is a no go along with the grits. We received burnt french toast bites that was also a NO GO. Our overall first time experience was very unpleasant hopefully it'll be better at another location.  This review is for the one on Decatur Ave.
Excellent service and great food! The blackened eggs benedict was the best Benedict I've ever had. Very clean and pleasant atmosphere.

Rating: 4.8 Stars  This place is fantastic. I only had the privilege of attending once, but it was totally worth the long wait. I was here back in May of 2019. My significant other and I checked in on Yelp, and we still had to wait for a while. I understand why. The location had a fun vibe, and the food was incredible. The coffee was fresh and tasted great. As a pancake lover--with cinnamon roll pancakes being my all-time favorite food--I naturally was ecstatic to see cinnamon swirl pancakes on the menu. That is why we choose to go here. They had excellent flavor and were not too sweet. I did not even need any syrup because of the great taste. I decided to be "healthy" and substitute fresh fruit as my side. This was also a good choice. My significant other ordered the bananas foster pain perdu, and this was also an extremely tasty meal. The next time I am back in New Orleans, I am 100% coming back here!
The food was pretty good expensive tho but was a nice portion sorry didn't get a pic.
Norman took very good care of me. The Belinis were very good also

Fast and friendly service once you get in...Shameka was an awesome server. I had the southern breakfast with pork sausage links. Thee best latte I’ve ever had! The mimosa was very good also. Sn: book your reservation on yelp before leave your hotel to minimize your wait.

We came for breakfast during the COVID Crisis right after Hurricane Laura.  Naturally it was empty. This place was very pleasant.  Service was excellent and food was good.  We're definitely going to visit the Nashville location when we get back.
Wonderful breakfast and the drinks were amazing. Every person was friendly and happy. I think this was my favorite eating spot this trip 😊
Highly recommend, every dish was tasteful,  service was great and welcoming,  and despite the wait time,  worth visiting.
I was only in NOLA for a weekend and this had to have been one of the best breakfasts I’ve ever had not to mention that incredible iced coffee that I can’t stop thinking of!
Best breakfast place in Nola, great food. But make sure you use the app to get yourself in the virtual line, as the wait times are long at times.
Killer eggs Benedict!!!!!
Great food
The only complaint I could possibly have is the wait to get in the door (because it's such a popular place). The food and service are always on par.
Food was really good and the staff was super friendly.  Highly recommend you go here if you want brunch.
The staff was friendly, the food was delicious, and wait time is reasonable considering the small space! Will definitely be coming here again!
The wait can be long so plan accordingly. I sat at the bar and waited about 5 minutes max. The blood Mary's were delicious and the food was amazing. Worth the wait if you want good food & drinks.

I love the venue and more importantly I love the food. I choose the double sampler of the eggs Benedict. One chicken and the other fried green tomato. Match that with a great cup of coffee and you are doing good. To me, it’s a must stop place no matter the line.
1 of my favorite places !

Ruby was a delicious treat. The food was excellent. Their biscuits where amazing! I'm not a biscuit aficionado but the one I dad there was better then the order of French toast we got. They serve it with special butter that cranks the delicious level to an 11. I would go back if I found myself in the big easy again.
The food was delicious! Highly recommend for brunch.
Fun breakfast spot. Helpful and friendly service.  Food was outstanding.  They can get very crowded so go early or be prepared for a waite .
Fantastic place to eat, fabulous pancakes, excellent service and reasonably priced.
Best breakfast/lunch place!

First place we stopped by as soon as we landed at the airport!  Overall, this place was pretty good if you're looking for a quick breakfast spot. My drink had no ice, while my husband had too much, but aside from that the food was really good!  Their BBQ shrimp & grits was amazing and tasted really well with their biscuit. My husband tried their spanish omelet, which was pretty tasty as well. Waiter was attentive and really appreciated that very much.  I would definitely make a reservation ahead of time, since this place does get busy/packed (especially on the weekends). Would definitely come back here again for brunch!
(Translated by Google) Deliz  (Original) Deliz
Amazing food
My dish was great, but my girlfriend didn't like the shrimp and grits. I'm no grits expert so can't speak to that personally 😏
was so good I got the grits and catfish and it was awsume
The food was okay. The atmosphere was great but it was a bit touristy

Went at 8:45am on a Saturday morning in February. Party of 2. Had to wait 10 minutes to get a table. Ordered the hot grilled salmon on brioche with poached egg, and the bread pudding pancake with chocolate. Both fantastic! Adding coffee and a chocolate milk, and a to-go chicken sandwich, the bill came to 50$ before tax. So, not expensive.
Food was fire. Showing love from dallas
Soooooo good!
Worth the wait. Excellent food. The maple butter with the biscuit is delicious.

Food was about the quality of IHOP, but at twice the cost. We waited over 30 minutes at about noon on a Monday. The food was lacking in flavor and character, not terrible, but nothing special. We had the lighter flair scramble, which doesn't include toast (for the price it should), so we paid $2 extra for toast which came out luke warm. We also had pancakes and a biscuit, all of which were just average for a cheaper breakfast place. We didn't try the various Benedict's which looked better. The noise was extremely loud as the place didn't have any noise blockers on the walls, so it echoed in a deafening hum.

No wait when we went on a Thursday.  The food was good.  I got The Peacemaker, which is any two benedicts, so I got the corner beef and the chicken St. Charles. Both were delicious. The rest of my party enjoyed their food. I would definitely recommend this if you're passing though New Orleans.
Awesome!! Loved this place. Ate here every morning. Tip: get there early. There are also more than one location around the city. Enjoy!! Its worth it.
Friendly team and great food! Will definitely be back!

Amazing food! I hate I can’t remember the Bartender’s name but he recently moved to Nola from Brooklyn. He was awesome, great conversation and he suggested the Grilled fish St. Peter. OMG. It was so good I almost ordered a second plate and I would’ve if I had room! Good spicy Bloody Mary with housemate mix needs no edit. I would highly recommend this spot for brunch!
Delicious breakfast!! A must stop when in New Orleans!
Love the breakfast!
Great food with huge portions, very tasty. Unique food offerings.
Delicious food- eggs, shrimp and -grits, fish, huge biscuits, maple butter. Courteous staff, Relatively fast service,  walk up bar for your morning eye opener

We were here during a very busy weekend in New Orleans. We had a party of 8 and we had to wait about 40 minutes to get a table. Once we were seated, the service was really good and food ordered was quickly delivered. I had biscuits with one having fried chicken and sauce and the other with pork and gravy... And an egg on top of both. Just wow and there was a lot of food. I ate half of each and then the remainder for dinner later. This was a nice change to the normal fare in New Orleans but still different and delicious.

The food was definitely worth the wait, although we didn’t have to wait a lot. The server was very friendly and there were pictures all over the wall. I had a hot cocoa and banana French Toast, which was a great choice. I would highly recommend visiting the Ruby slippers cafe. A suggestion I would have for them is to make space and add  a few more tables so the wait is not too long. However you should definitely visit.  *reviewed by my 10 year old.
Super long waits for just OK food. Staff were awesome, but not worth waiting a couple hours.
We came as a large rowdy group, our waitress was AMAZING. Renee C- best waitress we’ve had here in NOLA. Food was great. Quick and easy and super enjoyable.  Thanks Renee for making our morning!!

What a great breakfast/lunch find! We were staying at a hotel in the neighborhood and had the Croque Madame (ham, cheese, and egg sandwich with a side). Totally recommend it. We initially wanted dessert, but were too stuffed after our sandwiches. Try The Ruby Slipper!

Our food was ok. A bit flavorless which was a bummer because it looked and smelled delicious. The pumpkin filled french toast was pretty good. Our waitress was nice and informative. We didn't like that we were asked to move seats (while we were eating)  in order for someone else to occupy the seats we were on.
Great food. Went with the grilled st Peter fish
Quick service pleasant staff. Was busy today. Lots of events happening in the city this weekend.
Great place. Lots of good spins on classic breakfast dishes.
As always a must while in NOLA.
Not all the I ingredients were in the food when delivered.
Delicious french toast. Excellent service. Will go back again.
The white chocolate pancake,  just one, is PLENTY and the best food you'll ever put in your mouth.
Very rude staff, especially the waiter wearing dreadlocks.
Great food
Had the st Peter's fish and it was to die for!
Arielle was fantastic. The food was excellent. And the manager was great too! All around a great experience!
Good food
Superb menu, large portions, great servers. They really use technology well to manage the hour-plus wait. Multiple locations, all good.
Some great breakfast items that will leave you with you scratching your head on what to get as everything looks great. Wait to get in is about 90 minutes
Great brunch place, with tasty food and great breakfast drinks! Loved their Bloody Mary and the Milk Punch
Just a stunner of a breakfast, great service, food value...love this place!
Hands down the best place to get eggs benedict around!

We waited an hour after arriving at 1145. Tip: put yourself on the wait list on Yelp before making your way there! Saves time. We ordered the bloody Mary with bacon infused vodka, and the top 3 benedicts. Hands down the best Benedict ive ever had in my life. Life changing!

I must say I'm hard to please when it comes to food and what I consider good food. This place was recommended to me by various people that it was a must visit. After having a brunch here on 10/14/19 I must say that I wasn't as impressed with the food as everyone else was. I mean it was ok for what it was but not to have a long line waiting outside and all. But that's just my opinion. I did however really love the fried cheese grit thing that they had
The food is always great and the staff is fantastic.
It was 2 hours to get a table but the food was wonderful and very inexpensive and the service was great
I questioned the hour and a half wait, but after eating here I will gladly wait 2 hours. Food is amazing, staff is great and ambience is eclectic.
Amazeballs. The eggs Benedict might change your life. Bananas foster cocktail makes you feel like everything is good with the world.
(Translated by Google) Wari Kiomert, Ofina!  (Original) وری کیومرث، اوفینا!
Friendly staff and great breakfast/brunch. You won't be disappointed. Try the Spanish omelette and the creamy vanilla latte 😋
Excellent breakfast
Great spot.  Can't go wrong.

Best breakfast EVER! Our server Yanny was friendly, knowledgeable and most attentive.The Trifecta was extraordinary , the Bananas Foster Pain Perdu was great, the chorizo sausage and applewood-smoked bacon were delicious. A really true amazing experience!
I suggest their Chicken and Salmon Benedict. Great service as wel.

I heard from Jay that The Ruby Slipper has a very eclectic menu to choose from.  I wanted to try alot of them, so I went with his wife and we tried 8 of them.   They were all good.   5 stars.    Sports ball.  Rock and Roll.
Mckenzie was a delightful server for our visit! Food was delicious and service excellent. Wonderful ambiance as well!
Delicious breakfast! Loved the bananas foster pain perdu. Lots of good Benedicts.
Great little spot in the French Quarter
Holy NOLA!! If you’re looking for a tasty and hearty breakfast... Check out Ruby Slippers.

This place was pretty good, the food was excellent! Depending on what time of the day and what day you go, there is a pretty long wait time but what do you expect? The food speaks for itself and worth the wait.
The bacon infused bloody Mary was so good that I had to have TWO!   The food was also very well done!
Excellent food and service!

Perfect for a fast but good and traditional breakfast in New Orleans, you may find it a little crowded on the weekend but it’s pretty good. Good service, with a little delay but good. Read about the history of the place (how did they come after the Katrina in 2005), it’s pretty cool!! Prefer going to the Decatur St.
Super packed line. Didn’t eat, heard good things.
Great
Always great food and service. It's a must every time I visit New Orleans.

This place was recommended to us by a NO local we met in the airport. I couldn't quite bring myself to get the famous French toast dish, that would have floored my for the day. Instead I chose the eggs cochon and we also had the southern breakfast and bbq shrimp and grits. Everything was very tasty. The service was ok. Our waitress was nice, but a couple small things: no cream for the coffee when we sat down and being asked to give her our syrup for the next table was a little tacky. I came for breakfast, not to work. The eggs cochon was a pulled pork version of eggs Benedict, the eggs were great and the meat was tender. The biscuits were amazing and gigantic. I would recommend this place.
Food was great. I wish they'd gave us more greenery though

The food was good and the service was okay. We had the cochon and fried chicken benedicts but the eggs were overcooked with solid instead of runny yolks. The pork and the chicken was delicious. We also had the banana foster french bread which was a little too sweet but that's a matter of personal preference. Overall, there are better places to try in New Orleans than the Ruby Slipper for your breakfast needs.
This location is a bit smaller that others I've visited but it was still nice. The staff was courteous and attentive and the food was great!
The trifecta was the best eggs benedict I have ever had. Join the wailist from online.

I couldn't have been happier with my Southern Breakfast. The biscuit was massive and perfect texture, the maple butter was impressive, cheesy grits were just right, and they accommodated me as a vegetarian. The grapefruit juice is fresh squeezed!
Really good brunch selection
One of the best breakfast joints in NOLA! We also go at least once when were in town!
You must stop here for brunch!  The wait is worth every minute. The biscuit and gravy Benedict is a must!
Decent food but I prefer my bacon cooked.
Everything on the menu looked great. It was very hard to decide but the 3 little pigs omelette was fantastic.
Don't know why the lines are so long for this place. It's a descent breakfast. But it's far from excellent.
Great breakfast and great service.
Really good food and price

Ok boys and girls I have our place for breakfast in New Orleans! I have given you the best places to eat for breakfast from San Jose to Anaheim, Memphis to Myrtle Beach, the Windy City to Bean Town, and a Ron of places in between, so now we stop in the Big Easy for breakfast at Ruby’s Red Slipper!  The name derives not from Dorothy and Kansas, but from the notion of homecoming and it’s revival after Hurricane Katrina. Now this particular location is just off of Canal St. on Decatur, not to be confused with the location in the Business District. This is a small, more quaint, location with a “blink and you might miss it” door.  My son and I had no wait and were sat immediately. Unfortunately our waiter who was awesome, forfeited his right for a shout out by not introducing himself, but he doubled as the bartender so he was pretty busy in his defense.  If you have read any of my reviews on breakfast, you know that it all starts with the coffee. It must be in a decent size mug, hot, and be kept full. This was some of the best tasting coffee I have EVER HAD, grown right here in NOLA.  There is something to be said about eating in New Orleans. As one of the culinary capitals of the world you will find classic dishes and ingredients jumbled together in a Mad Scientist style manner. Such was the case with my sons Eggs Benedict which he usually is a traditionalist. In this case they used a fluffy buttermilk biscuit, with poached eggs, glazed bacon, and hollandaise sauce. He left absolutely nothing but the plate.  As for me, I was the big winner! Going completely off book, I took the waiters advise on the daily special and was sooo glad I did. It was a Chicken Viera that started with a base of goat cheese grits ( I know I know I had to contemplate that one too) with a homemade salsa at one end of the banana bowl and a green chili sauce at the other end. In the center was a pulled chicken and scrambled egg. Again the ingredients on their own would cause for pause, but together it was outstanding! The dish was complimented with a buttermilk biscuit of my own, with a tasty brown sugar cinnamon spread.  At the end of the day when in NOLA you have to expand your palate and try new things that don’t sound like they should go together. I don’t give away five stars for just any restaurant but the Ruby Slipper will now be on my can’t miss list when visiting the Big Easy to start my day!
